ENGL 1127
Students will receive credit for either ENGL 1127 or ENGL 1128 but not both.

Students planning to enrol in a first-semester English course must take the Langara English Test (LET) or Language Proficiency Index Test (LPI) prior to the semester in which they want to register. Students who have BC English 12 or BC English Literature 12 or equivalent with an 80% are not required to write the LET or LPI.

Students not meeting those exemptions need the following scores on LET or LPI:
LET 3 or LPI 26 on the essay with one of the following:
5/10 or higher in sentence structure; or
5/10 or higher in English usage; or
10/20 or higher in reading comprehension.

Students who have scored a level 3 on the LET (or 26/40 with a 5 or higher in English usage on the LPI) are also strongly encouraged to register in English 1121 (there is no tuition charge for this course) in order to upgrade their reading and writing skills. English 1121 will help students at this prerequisite level succeed in ENGL 1127 which is the university transfer course.

See calendar for course descriptions. Students with LET or LPI level 5 should enrol in ENGL 1128.

Exploring Literature

  

2

 Lecture M-W---- 1230-1420 08-Sep-09 04-Dec-09

A321

 Jacqueline Weal
                  ENGL 2237, section 001 is "Transformers: Shape-shifters in Literature & Culture".
"Transformers" is an interdisciplinary odyssey into the strange - characters will metamorphose into frogs, werewolves, vampires, insects, degenerates and cyborgs. These shape-shifters will make us see and think differently by literally embodying change. In our survey of transformations, we will examine characters and themes from a variety of critical perspectives, including sartorial, sociological, scientific and more. Although this is a literature course, we'll view film clips and look at websites for additional perspectives on shape-shifting.
